♪ If love ends in vengeance ♪

15
00:01:36,575 --> 00:01:40,885
♪ Will you still embrace it? ♪

16
00:01:41,904 --> 00:01:48,501
♪ If love is gained
in exchange for someone's life ♪

17
00:01:49,156 --> 00:01:57,880
♪ Will you still say this love
is what you wanted? ♪

18
00:01:58,873 --> 00:02:00,246
- Hey!
- My lord!

19
00:02:00,326 --> 00:02:01,156
Saeng!

20
00:02:01,229 --> 00:02:03,036
It was your plan all along.

21
00:02:03,230 --> 00:02:04,349
You set me up!

22
00:02:04,422 --> 00:02:05,955
The mastermind behind it all,

23
00:02:06,182 --> 00:02:07,150
is the Viscount!

24
00:02:07,270 --> 00:02:08,284
Not me!

25
00:02:10,369 --> 00:02:12,289
Why bother when they don't give a damn?

26
00:02:12,503 --> 00:02:13,580
Better to exact revenge

27
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:15,593
and revel in his lavish inheritance!

28
00:02:32,756 --> 00:02:33,796
Ms. Ramphoei!

29
00:02:34,126 --> 00:02:35,006
What is it, Chaem?

30
00:02:35,177 --> 00:02:36,177
It's terrible.

31
00:02:36,489 --> 00:02:38,156
What's wrong? Is it the Viscount?

32
00:02:39,584 --> 00:02:41,030
How did you know

33
00:02:41,055 --> 00:02:42,930
that this is about my lord?

34
00:02:45,016 --> 00:02:46,430
Isn't he the most important person

35
00:02:46,455 --> 00:02:47,295
in the estate?

36
00:02:47,463 --> 00:02:49,886
Stop blabbering and spit it out.

37
00:02:50,533 --> 00:02:52,019
My Lord is in trouble.

38
00:02:52,533 --> 00:02:53,572
Take me to him.

39
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:54,620
Yes, ma'am.

40
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:56,220
This way.

41
00:03:12,706 --> 00:03:14,860
Chaem said that you were in trouble.

42
00:03:16,606 --> 00:03:17,619
Just a trivial matter.

43
00:03:18,192 --> 00:03:19,315
Why the need to report it

44
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:20,335
to your mistress?

45
00:03:22,470 --> 00:03:24,402
So, what's the matter, my lord?

46
00:03:25,423 --> 00:03:27,291
His shoelace broke before entering,

47
00:03:27,424 --> 00:03:29,077
then he tripped and sprained his ankle.

48
00:03:29,557 --> 00:03:30,678
It's nothing serious.

49
00:03:38,486 --> 00:03:39,486
Chaem!

50
00:03:39,706 --> 00:03:41,013
What were you thinking?

51
00:03:41,246 --> 00:03:42,625
This is utter nonsense!

52
00:03:42,725 --> 00:03:43,905
He's fine.

53
00:03:45,286 --> 00:03:46,699
Apologies, ma'am.

54
00:03:47,074 --> 00:03:48,074
What?

55
00:03:48,227 --> 00:03:49,907
Must I bleed

56
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,373
for you to be satisfied?

57
00:03:51,930 --> 00:03:52,930
No need to worry.

58
00:03:53,174 --> 00:03:54,554
I'm not so weak that I'd perish

59
00:03:54,754 --> 00:03:56,960
for you to indulge in my inheritance.

60
00:03:59,007 --> 00:03:59,866
Dech.

61
00:03:59,873 --> 00:04:01,708
Carry my bag into the office.

62
00:04:02,183 --> 00:04:03,183
Yes, my lord.

63
00:04:03,483 --> 00:04:04,862
Will you be alright, my lord?

64
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:25,264
Please don't take it to heart, ma'am.

65
00:04:25,825 --> 00:04:27,173
He must be feeling irritated

66
00:04:27,198 --> 00:04:28,278
by his injury.

67
00:05:23,713 --> 00:05:24,713
Damn it.

68
00:06:28,318 --> 00:06:29,691
You've treated me well.

69
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,246
I'll visit you more often.

70
00:06:33,496 --> 00:06:34,496
Please do, sir.

71
00:06:36,242 --> 00:06:38,062
Sir, you're so kind to me.

72
00:06:39,095 --> 00:06:40,687
It's my happiness and pleasure

73
00:06:41,161 --> 00:06:42,781
to be able to serve you.

74
00:06:43,038 --> 00:06:44,871
Be consistent about it,

75
00:06:46,991 --> 00:06:48,471
and I'll get you out of here.

76
00:06:51,404 --> 00:06:52,404
You're not joking?

77
00:06:53,828 --> 00:06:55,154
If you do,

78
00:06:55,488 --> 00:06:57,825
I'll do anything you ask of me.

79
00:06:58,258 --> 00:07:00,685
Even in the afterlife,
I shall serve you, sir.

80
00:07:05,197 --> 00:07:06,197
I'm leaving.

81
00:07:15,357 --> 00:07:17,263
I love you, my lord.

82
00:07:19,983 --> 00:07:22,166
I really can't do it.

83
00:07:31,843 --> 00:07:37,163
♪ If love ends in vengeance ♪

84
00:07:38,737 --> 00:07:43,047
♪ Will you still embrace it? ♪

85
00:07:44,335 --> 00:07:50,932
♪ If love is gained
in exchange for someone's life ♪

86
00:07:59,364 --> 00:08:00,484
It's so quiet.

87
00:08:00,664 --> 00:08:01,957
Has she gone to sleep?

88
00:08:02,264 --> 00:08:03,849
You mean Ms. Ramphoei?

89
00:08:03,989 --> 00:08:07,102
Who else would it be?
Isn't she the one you serve?

90
00:08:08,303 --> 00:08:09,712
I apologize, my lord.

91
00:08:10,248 --> 00:08:12,721
Ms. Ramphoei went out this evening.

92
00:08:13,198 --> 00:08:14,657
She might be at the musical or

93
00:08:14,665 --> 00:08:16,777
having a meal at the shopping district.

94
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:32,178
Dech.

95
00:08:44,550 --> 00:08:45,550
Dech!

96
00:08:57,418 --> 00:08:58,418
You damn Ramphoei.

97
00:09:32,628 --> 00:09:33,628
You're here.

98
00:09:34,395 --> 00:09:35,395
You coward.

99
00:09:38,168 --> 00:09:39,913
You couldn't do such an easy task?

100
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:43,015
You two. Don't get too cocky now.

101
00:09:43,376 --> 00:09:45,216
You think I'm oblivious to your plan?

102
00:09:45,425 --> 00:09:47,444
I know you'll get rid of me

103
00:09:47,469 --> 00:09:49,242
after I kill the Viscount.

104
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:53,557
I may be drunk,

105
00:09:53,932 --> 00:09:55,265
but I'm not stupid.

106
00:09:56,014 --> 00:09:57,974
Listen well, both of you.

107
00:09:58,134 --> 00:09:59,342
Don't you dare

108
00:09:59,367 --> 00:10:01,502
plot against the Viscount again.

109
00:10:03,236 --> 00:10:04,243
What will you do?

110
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:08,274
If you try to harm him,

111
00:10:09,381 --> 00:10:10,381
I...

112
00:10:10,574 --> 00:10:12,494
I will be the one protecting him.

113
00:10:13,580 --> 00:10:14,580
One day,

114
00:10:14,856 --> 00:10:17,747
he'll know that I'm more loyal to him.

115
00:10:17,772 --> 00:10:19,102
Much more than you!

116
00:10:19,127 --> 00:10:20,362
and Dech!

117
00:10:25,784 --> 00:10:27,023
Don't do it, Phoem!

118
00:10:27,637 --> 00:10:28,791
I'll fight to the death.

119
00:10:32,870 --> 00:10:33,870
Try it.

120
00:10:34,597 --> 00:10:36,856
Your knife against my ax.

121
00:10:37,793 --> 00:10:39,270
Who will meet their end first?

122
00:10:43,256 --> 00:10:44,256
Saeng,

123
00:10:44,616 --> 00:10:46,522
you think you can get out of this

124
00:10:46,555 --> 00:10:47,555
alive?

125
00:10:50,146 --> 00:10:51,453
Don't know, don't care.

126
00:10:51,711 --> 00:10:53,460
But I know that if I report you and

127
00:10:53,485 --> 00:10:56,324
your whereabouts to the officials,

128
00:10:56,805 --> 00:10:59,438
you'll be no better than the street dogs!

129
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:01,059
Wait, Phoem!

130
00:11:03,325 --> 00:11:06,460
Are you going against me, Saeng?

131
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:10,441
You stupid, brainless mongrel.

132
00:11:10,606 --> 00:11:11,991
- If you...
- Oh, shut up!

133
00:11:13,925 --> 00:11:15,771
Don't try to pit me against my lord!

134
00:11:17,338 --> 00:11:19,357
Your tricks won't work on me anymore.

135
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,725
You better be careful.

136
00:11:24,777 --> 00:11:25,790
If I expose you

137
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:27,045
for your debaucheries.

138
00:11:27,973 --> 00:11:31,109
You're the one he'll send packing!

139
00:11:33,270 --> 00:11:35,003
Saeng! You low life!

140
00:11:37,845 --> 00:11:38,845
Nah.

141
00:11:41,540 --> 00:11:42,740
Don't even try.

142
00:12:14,855 --> 00:12:15,855
Dech.

143
00:12:19,801 --> 00:12:21,434
What is that gun for, my lord?

144
00:12:22,273 --> 00:12:23,280
Did something happen?

145
00:12:23,921 --> 00:12:25,567
Was there a burglar, my lord?

146
00:12:26,680 --> 00:12:27,767
Where did you go, Dech?

147
00:12:28,075 --> 00:12:29,367
You weren't in your room.

148
00:12:29,568 --> 00:12:30,955
Mai wasn't feeling well,

149
00:12:31,342 --> 00:12:32,342
so I asked Dech

150
00:12:32,362 --> 00:12:33,942
to take him to the pharmacy.

151
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:36,094
Kam feared they might be closed.

152
00:12:36,321 --> 00:12:38,103
So I talked to the owner for him

153
00:12:38,128 --> 00:12:39,530
and got the medications.

154
00:12:43,161 --> 00:12:44,274
What about Ramphoei?

155
00:12:44,714 --> 00:12:45,714
Does anyone see her?

156
00:12:48,468 --> 00:12:50,320
I heard you mention my name.

157
00:12:50,593 --> 00:12:52,070
Did you miss me, my lord?

158
00:12:53,237 --> 00:12:55,634
Where were you when it's this dark?

159
00:12:55,866 --> 00:12:57,239
Forgot you had a home?

160
00:12:58,628 --> 00:13:00,080
Home was dull,

161
00:13:00,289 --> 00:13:01,000
so I decided

162
00:13:01,007 --> 00:13:02,287
to take a stroll at the fair.

163
00:13:03,193 --> 00:13:04,193
A fair?

164
00:13:04,696 --> 00:13:05,923
There's no fair today.

165
00:13:06,224 --> 00:13:07,836
There's one near the market.

166
00:13:11,852 --> 00:13:14,552
As for why I wasn't home.

167
00:13:14,732 --> 00:13:15,732
There's nothing to do

168
00:13:15,738 --> 00:13:17,258
when my husband isn't interested.

169
00:13:17,950 --> 00:13:18,790
Or perhaps

170
00:13:18,815 --> 00:13:20,937
you're seeking some attention tonight?

171
00:13:21,190 --> 00:13:22,597
I'll pay you a visit, my lord.

172
00:13:23,724 --> 00:13:24,724
Shameless!

173
00:13:32,782 --> 00:13:34,068
Please be careful.

174
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:36,227
I don't know where you went

175
00:13:36,794 --> 00:13:37,794
and I won't always

176
00:13:37,819 --> 00:13:38,873
be there to save you.

177
00:13:39,931 --> 00:13:40,884
Thanks.

178
00:13:40,909 --> 00:13:42,553
Next time, I'll be careful.

179
00:13:44,060 --> 00:13:45,060
Kam.

180
00:13:45,307 --> 00:13:47,175
If you're not smart, just shut it.

181
00:13:47,718 --> 00:13:49,412
Because if I'm in trouble,

182
00:13:49,779 --> 00:13:51,805
I'm not going down without you.

183
00:13:52,133 --> 00:13:53,133
Got it?

184
00:13:53,369 --> 00:13:54,729
I'm sorry, ma'am.

185
00:13:59,211 --> 00:14:00,211
Hey.

186
00:14:00,859 --> 00:14:02,246
Stop worrying about her

187
00:14:02,693 --> 00:14:03,832
and look after yourself.

188
00:14:04,445 --> 00:14:05,445
I don't know how long

189
00:14:05,452 --> 00:14:06,631
I can keep this a secret.

190
00:14:10,519 --> 00:14:11,519
Thanks, man.

191
00:14:19,660 --> 00:14:21,013
Aren't you wicked, Dech?

192
00:14:21,233 --> 00:14:22,593
I didn't expect someone

193
00:14:22,618 --> 00:14:24,620
as naive as you to be embezzling.

194
00:14:26,379 --> 00:14:31,332
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

195
00:14:31,394 --> 00:14:36,347
(House of the Dark Shadows
novel: Phakhinai, screenplay: Wannason)

196
00:14:36,808 --> 00:14:37,848
You're lucky.

197
00:14:38,329 --> 00:14:40,109
I saw him on his way to your room,

198
00:14:40,782 --> 00:14:42,462
so I got to you first.

199
00:14:42,733 --> 00:14:43,933
It could've been bad.

200
00:14:44,741 --> 00:14:46,960
He even had a gun ready in his hand!

201
00:14:49,147 --> 00:14:51,273
From now on, I'll be more careful.

202
00:14:52,321 --> 00:14:53,321
Lately,

203
00:14:53,415 --> 00:14:55,711
I know that you miss her,

204
00:14:55,736 --> 00:14:57,437
but aren't your visits too frequent?

205
00:14:58,118 --> 00:14:59,684
If the Viscount catches you,

206
00:15:00,632 --> 00:15:02,766
our plan will go down the drain.

207
00:15:07,830 --> 00:15:08,954
Thanks for the warning,

208
00:15:09,046 --> 00:15:10,019
my man.

209
00:15:11,087 --> 00:15:12,087
Sure.

210
00:15:12,747 --> 00:15:13,919
Think long and hard.

211
00:15:40,951 --> 00:15:42,850
At first, I didn't
think much about it.

212
00:15:43,817 --> 00:15:45,136
But then I realized

213
00:15:45,490 --> 00:15:46,747
you thought that I had

214
00:15:46,771 --> 00:15:48,536
sneaked out with Ms. Ramphoei

215
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:50,510
and was going to shoot me dead.

216
00:15:57,834 --> 00:15:58,905
I'm sorry, Dech.

217
00:15:59,623 --> 00:16:00,623
From now on,

218
00:16:01,443 --> 00:16:02,896
I won't be so hasty.

219
00:16:04,373 --> 00:16:05,666
Please forgive me, Dech.

220
00:16:07,323 --> 00:16:08,323
Please.

221
00:16:12,186 --> 00:16:13,186
Alright, my lord.

222
00:16:18,688 --> 00:16:20,301
If you've truly forgiven me,

223
00:16:20,468 --> 00:16:21,468
Can I...

224
00:16:22,088 --> 00:16:23,381
stay the night here?

225
00:17:25,989 --> 00:17:27,282
All done, my lord.

226
00:17:28,399 --> 00:17:29,445
Don't you have to

227
00:17:29,470 --> 00:17:31,070
meet the Duke today?

228
00:17:31,678 --> 00:17:33,275
Oh, you're right.

229
00:17:34,209 --> 00:17:35,454
Thanks for reminding me.

230
00:17:37,841 --> 00:17:39,162
Go get dressed, my lord.

231
00:17:39,169 --> 00:17:41,035
I'll meet you in the front yard.

232
00:17:41,423 --> 00:17:43,023
I'll go fetch your bag for you.

233
00:17:44,234 --> 00:17:45,240
Thanks.

234
00:17:46,241 --> 00:17:47,241
Of course.

235
00:18:08,509 --> 00:18:09,509
My lord!

236
00:18:13,092 --> 00:18:14,772
What's the matter, Ms. Ramphoei?

237
00:18:16,420 --> 00:18:17,753
Looks like he isn't here.

238
00:18:17,787 --> 00:18:19,446
I just need some extra money.

239
00:18:19,714 --> 00:18:21,380
I'll come again in the evening.

240
00:18:21,980 --> 00:18:23,407
Hold on, Ms. Ramphoei.

241
00:18:25,585 --> 00:18:26,512
What?

242
00:18:26,537 --> 00:18:27,885
Are you giving me money?

243
00:19:00,745 --> 00:19:02,052
Aren't you wicked, Dech?

244
00:19:02,298 --> 00:19:03,565
I didn't expect someone

245
00:19:03,590 --> 00:19:05,884
as naive as you to be embezzling.

246
00:19:07,303 --> 00:19:08,303
That's not it.

247
00:19:09,178 --> 00:19:10,178
This is from the farmers

248
00:19:10,185 --> 00:19:11,999
who couldn't pay rent with money,

249
00:19:12,023 --> 00:19:13,817
so they paid with fruits.

250
00:19:15,802 --> 00:19:16,802
And?

251
00:19:17,962 --> 00:19:19,994
The Viscount let me handle it.

252
00:19:20,468 --> 00:19:22,187
So I sold their produce.

253
00:19:22,508 --> 00:19:23,896
This is what I got.

254
00:19:24,799 --> 00:19:25,632
Not bad.

255
00:19:25,747 --> 00:19:27,529
You're smarter than I thought.

256
00:19:28,771 --> 00:19:30,977
Even without his salary,

257
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:32,857
with all the lands the Viscount owns,

258
00:19:33,462 --> 00:19:34,645
I believe

259
00:19:34,670 --> 00:19:36,993
I can make the most out of it,

260
00:19:37,420 --> 00:19:38,420
to the point where

261
00:19:38,430 --> 00:19:40,223
we can all live comfortably.

262
00:20:40,472 --> 00:20:42,056
I'll take it from here.

263
00:20:42,263 --> 00:20:43,598
You should go back.

264
00:21:37,504 --> 00:21:39,583
You care so much for your apprearance.

265
00:21:40,656 --> 00:21:42,762
If you could see your current state,

266
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:46,182
you'd be screaming in horror.

267
00:21:51,253 --> 00:21:52,253
Bu-nga,

268
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:55,013
do you still remember?

269
00:21:58,661 --> 00:22:00,227
The first time we met,

270
00:22:01,989 --> 00:22:04,982
You taught me about bravery,

271
00:22:07,654 --> 00:22:09,620
and taught me about strength.

272
00:22:35,997 --> 00:22:37,170
Excuse me.

273
00:22:37,498 --> 00:22:39,037
What did you say? Speak louder.

274
00:22:40,235 --> 00:22:41,661
Excuse me.

275
00:22:41,996 --> 00:22:43,435
Did you hear anything?

276
00:22:44,308 --> 00:22:45,308
Yeah,

277
00:22:45,596 --> 00:22:46,596
but not clearly.

278
00:22:46,783 --> 00:22:49,396
Sounds like a fly buzzing in my ears.

279
00:22:49,609 --> 00:22:50,936
Very annoying.

280
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:52,572
I beg to differ.

281
00:22:52,736 --> 00:22:54,576
Doesn't it sound more like

282
00:22:54,601 --> 00:22:56,570
that of an unwanted bastard?

283
00:23:02,727 --> 00:23:03,974
What a klutz,

284
00:23:04,188 --> 00:23:05,660
